📌 Topic: WHERE Clause – This is used to filter rows based on a specific condition. It helps us retrieve only the data that meets certain criteria instead of fetching everything.

💻 Example Query:
SELECT * 
FROM EMPLOYEES
WHERE SALARY > 50000;

📝 Explanation:
 This query will display only those employees whose Salary is greater than 50,000.
 It is useful when we want to analyze a specific subset of our data.
